headline: US Regulators Mull Easing Banks' Capital Rule on Treasury Trades
summary: U.S. Regulators weigh cutting SLR by up to 1.5 percentage points to boost trading at top banks like JPM, GS, MS & WFC in the $29T U.S. Treasury market.

headline: Goldman Sachs Estimates $10 a Barrel Oil Risk Premium Amid Mideast Tensions
summary: Goldman Sachs estimated a geopolitical risk premium of around $10 a barrel after Brent surged following Israel’s attack on Iran, adding that while the futures curve suggests much higher prices were likely in the next few months, it also reflected limited changes to the long-term outlook.

headline: SPAC Comeback Draws Renewed Interest from Wall Street
summary: According to SPACInsider data, there have been 58 SPAC offerings so far this year, one more than the total in all of 2024.
